# Test / production boundary

## No test-only exports in Libraries/

Test helpers belong in `tests/harness/`, not `Libraries/`.

- Do **not** add `resetFooForTests`, `clearFooPools`, `getFooPoolSize`, or assert helpers to production modules.
- If a test needs isolation (IDs, pools, slab pose checks), build it in `tests/harness/` importing production APIs — or fix production to be session-scoped so tests get isolation from fresh session construction.

Before adding any new export under `Libraries/`, run:

```powershell
node scripts/audit-test-leaks.mjs
```

## No production branches for tests

- No optional constructor modes, null `state` stubs, or `if (test)` paths in production to keep tests easy.
- Tests must construct real runtime wiring (`KineticSession`, `WorldObstacleGrid`, registry, …) or use harness factories.

See also `no-shims-and-guards.mdc`, `.agents/AGENTS.md`.

## Mock consolidation

- Reuse `tests/harness/kineticTickHarness.js`, `kineticSlabHarness.js`, `kineticContactHarness.js`, `worldPropHarness.js`, `wallSegmentHarness.js`.
- Do **not** define `function mock*` / `function createMock*` in `tests/*.test.js` when the shape is reused — extend harness instead.
- Canvas mocks: `tests/mockCanvas2d.js`.

## Review bar

- New `Libraries/` export imported only from `tests/`? → Move to harness or delete.
- Test file defines inline mock used in one place only? → OK; used 2+ times? → Harness.
- Production code changed solely because a test couldn't set up state? → Fix the test harness, revert the prod branch.
